    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <head>208. Telegram 748 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d208fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/9–2055.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-09-20"
                            >September 20, 1955, 1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d208-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d208-1"/>
                <p>748. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Re telcon with <persName corresp="#p_RWS_1">Robertson</persName>, regret
                    necessity replacing either <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1">Clough</persName> or
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDN_1">Forman</persName> at this time. Both have done
                    excellent work and are very helpful to me. Had hoped when replacement made he
                    could have had advantage intimate association over a period with Departmental
                    work on these talks. However, realize pressure work in GA may make earlier
                    action imperative. Balancing all considerations, including Department’s needs
                    and new phase talks entering here, believe best <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1"
                        >Clough</persName> return. Hope whoever sent will be given maximum
                    opportunity familiarize self with Department’s thinking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Shillock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Note: Delayed in transmission.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
